---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Quickstart" description="Get BridgeAIChat running across a control host and one agent device.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Quickstart</div>
    <h1>Bring up the beta in three moves.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Preferred path on macOS is Homebrew. If you are testing before the tap is public, use the packaged release
      installers instead. The runtime shape stays the same either way.
    </p>
    <div class="status section"><strong>Beta note:</strong> Codex is the smoothest first-run path today. Claude works, but local auth and quota state still matter on the device.</div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap step-list">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Install and start the control host</p>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-app
bridge-gateway</pre>
      <p class="muted">Fallback beta path: download the matching <code>bridge-app</code> release and run <code>bash install-app.sh</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Install one agent on another machine</p>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-agent
bash "$(brew --prefix)/share/bridge-agent/install-agent.sh"</pre>
      <p class="muted">The installer creates <code>~/.bridge-agent/agent.yaml</code>, prompts for the gateway URL, and can register the agent as a startup service.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Open the UI and send a test prompt</p>
      <pre>open http://localhost:8080</pre>
      <p class="muted">Once the device shows as online, send a simple prompt like <code>hi</code> or <code>what directory are you in?</code> to validate the flow.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Gateway URL</div>
      <h2>What the agent needs</h2>
      <pre>gateway:
  url: ws://100.x.x.x:8080/agent</pre>
      <p>Use the control host's Tailscale IP or MagicDNS name so the remote device can reach the gateway privately.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Requirements</div>
      <h2>Before you start</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Tailscale on the control host and every agent device</li>
        <li><code>tmux</code> installed on every agent device</li>
        <li>A supported AI CLI on the agent device, such as Codex or Claude</li>
        <li>The gateway running before the first agent attempts to connect</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
